# Lean build context for the dashboard image.
#
# Strategy: deny everything, then re-include ONLY the two runtime paths the image
# needs. This guarantees .git, .worktrees, docs/ (real run artifacts), tests,
# other scripts (pr_resolver.py, release.py, validate_marketplace.py), and
# __pycache__ never enter the build context — nothing but the server + its baked
# UI assets is available to COPY.
*

# Re-include only the runtime files (NOT a blanket !scripts/, which would readmit
# tests and unrelated tooling). Docker needs the directory entries re-included so
# the traversal reaches the files below.
!scripts
scripts/*
!scripts/dashboard_server.py
!scripts/dashboard_assets
scripts/dashboard_assets/*
!scripts/dashboard_assets/**
